keys.example: compound directories containing identified Bruker directories and JEOL files; Bruker directories missing n/

keys: This is an excellent example, other than that it is missing structures.
Each compound's directory contains one or more Bruker directories and/or JEOL jdf files.
Unfortunately, these are missing their numbered directories and so are not readable by TopSpin.
matches '1h/1h-13C/', assigning '1h' to the compound id and '1h-13C' to the data objec id
matches '1h/1h-1H.jdf', assigning '1h' to the compound id and '1h-1H' to the data objec id
